If you grew up frugal it feels so wasteful to go out and spend like 30 bucks total getting lunch with a friend outdoors then getting an ice cream and maybe a beer together but when ur making decent money it really doesn't matter. Takes time to get used to it, but it just doesn't.

No one ever goes bankrupt over buying a few fun drinks and a dessert when out and about with others once or twice a week, when you're working it's basically always worth it to waste a few dozen euros on nothing to destress and relax even if it goes against your natural instincts.

It's like Evola making fun of Sartre for being too stingy with money. You're meant to spend some of it. But if you grew up relatively poor with little pocket money as a kid it still always feels like you're being wasteful buying yourself stuff and not being as frugal as possible.
